				<p class="text privacy_section_header">Job description</p>
					<li class="text terms_li_no_bullet">As a writer, your role will be to research upcoming legislation, breakdown and synthesis the information and pass it on to the Editor in Chief. The work will be Part-time based on when Bills are introduced to Parliament.</li>

				<p class="text privacy_section_header">Qualities needed</p>
					<li class="text terms_li_no_bullet">Impeccable time management. The ability to work in a deadline driven environment is a must.</li>
					<li class="text terms_li_no_bullet">The ability to quickly understand and summarise vast amounts of information.</li>
					<li class="text terms_li_no_bullet">A solid understanding of the Westminster political system and the Parliamentary process. </li>

				<p class="text privacy_section_header">Payment</p>
					<li class="text terms_li_no_bullet">Hourly or per-piece.</li>

				<p class="text privacy_section_header">Application</p> 
					<li class="text terms_li_no_bullet">To apply: send the following to <a href="mailto:contact@whip.org.uk">contact@whip.org.uk</a></li>
					<li class="text terms_li_no_bullet">CV/Cover letter</li>
					<li class="text terms_li_no_bullet">A written sample of a legislation breakdown i.e pick a piece of previous legislation and summarise it into the layout below:</li>
					<li class="text terms_li_no_bullet">- Your own Bill title</li>
					<li class="text terms_li_no_bullet">- The meaning of the Bill  (30-50 words)</li>
